-- Tata Power, Medco Energi Shortlisted for Indonesia Geothermal Power Plan
-- Bambang Djanuarto
-- 2010-08-06T06:06:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-06/tata-power-medco-energi-shortlisted-for-indonesia-geothermal-power-plan.html

          
          
             -- Tata Power Co. and PT Medco Energi
Internasional have been shortlisted to develop a 200-megawatt
geothermal project in North Sumatra, Sugiharto Harsoprayitno,
geothermal director at the Indonesian energy ministry said.  
 The government will make a decision this week, he said in
Jakarta today. Medco has teamed up with Itochu Corp. to bid for
the project, Harsoprayitno said.  
